OAO Opin, a Russian real estate
developer owned by metals billionaire  Mikhail Prokhorov , swung
to profit in the first half as the housing market rebounded.  Net income was $21 million in the six months ended June 30
compared with a $61.3 million loss a year earlier, the company
formerly known as Open Investments said today in an e-mailed
statement. Sales surged 80 percent to $114.5 million.  To contact the reporter on this story:
